import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='normal', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["normal"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'normal' values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='day', y='actual', data=data, label='Actual')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='day', y='forecast', data=data, label='Forecast')
    chart.set_title("How do the 'actual' values compare to the 'forecast' values?", wrap=True)
    chart.axhline(data['actual'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean Actual')
    chart.axhline(data['forecast'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Mean Forecast')
    chart.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['difference'] = pd.to_numeric(data['difference'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='difference', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['difference'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["difference"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the 'difference' values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
